<head>KNOT</head><list type="translations"><item xml:lang="zh">扣子</item></list>
<div type="definition">
<p>THREADS OR ROPES PUT TOGETHER so as to CAUSE it TO be DIFFICULT to MUTUALLY REMOVE them from each other.</p></div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The specialised word for a knot is niǔ 紐.</p>
<p>2. Jié 結 "tie up" is also used to refer to what is tied up, a knot.</p></div>
